The Herald Sports Reporter
THE Premier Soccer League have postponed the match between Triangle United and Ngezi Platinum Stars after players and officials tested Covid-19 positive. The match was scheduled for this Saturday. According to a statement by the PSL spokesperson Kudzai Bare, some Triangle players and officials tested positive during routine testing. “This serves to advise that the Chibuku Super Cup match between Triangle United FC and Ngezi Platinum Stars Fc scheduled to be played on Saturday 3 July 2021 has been postponed. This is to allow Triangle players and officials who have tested positive for Covid-19 to self-isolate in line with Covid-19 protocols. “Clubs are reminded to follow the Covid-19 protocols and guidelines to contain the spread of the virus.
The postponed fixture will be rearranged in due course,” wrote Bare.